title: For Sale:  WWI French 1892 Revolver + orig. Holster + orig. Ammo
postcontent: For sale is a World War I war horse. A model 1892 French Revolver in 8mm French. EXCELLENT original condition. Dated 1899. Cylinder timing is perfect. Functions smoothly and strongly with crisp trigger pull like a modern revolver. Sights are unique to this model and very good for target aquisition. These were favorites of the French Foreign Legion before, during and after WWI, as well as French Resistance fighters and some Nazi soldiers during World War II. In fact, a few days ago a cache buried in Latvia during WWII was discovered with a preserved Mle 1892 revovler just like the one offered here. The revolver, along with other supplies and explosives, was left for saboteurs in the area! (article is on guns.com and is titled "70 year old saboteur cache looks like it was buried yesterday (17 PHOTOS)").Lots of history and a good shooter! Ammo can be reloaded or purchased from a few places online. -Comes with the original holster which is in great condition as well. postcontent: Up for sell is an original, all numbers matching 1968 Enfield RFI Ishapore 2a1. If you aren't familiar with this weapon, let me give you a back story. This rifle was used by the Indian Army and was one of the last primary bolt action rifle used in combat, other than specialized sniper rifles. This rifle was manufactured in 1968. This rifle is based on the .303 Enfield MKIII SMLE platform, but is specifically manufactured and chambered in 7.62x51. The stock is a No.1 MKIII Enfield stock. The removable magazine holds 12rds and you can still purchase spare magazines on GunBroker for about $50. This particular rifle is designed for the use of stripper clips. The bore is bright and shiny and rifling is very strong! The headspace has been checked by a gunsmith and it can shoot standard commercial 308 ammo. I on the other hand, have only shot 7.62x51 ammo through it. For being 47years old, this rifle is impeccable. There are no import markings on this rifle, just original stamped Enfield numbers. All serials match, including on the receiver, bolt, nose cap, magazine, and rear sight. Asking $375obo. I also have more pictures available if requested. title: For Sale:  Dan Wesson Eco 9mm NIB
location: Holly springs, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
NIB Dan Wesson 9mm ECO for sale.    Never fired, new in box.  All paperwork, 2 mags, etc, perfect carry size..ONLY TRADES CONSIDERED WOULD BE WILSON COMBAT or NIGHTHAWK in 45 or 9mm - NOTHING ELSE, THANKS!
There has never been a higher demand for self defense handguns than there is today. The greatest demand is for the smallest, lightest gun available, but this has drawbacks. Generally these guns are difficult to shoot well, lack stopping power and recoil can be a problem. If you can’t hit or stop what you are shooting at, what good is the handgun? We can understand all of these concerns as we face them every day as well. We wanted to give our customers the smallest, lightest gun that we could without sacrificing accuracy, dependability and stopping power.
Presenting the ECO, a true single stack officer size 1911 weighing in at only 25 oz. For years the officer 1911 has been criticized for reliability. We have taken care of that by using some of the latest technology as well as our background in doing what others say can’t be done. This gun has all the latest and greatest we have to offer.
The ECO wears tritium night sights with our tactical ledge sight on the rear of our lightweight 3.5” slide. The barrel is a flush-cut ramped bull barrel with target crown rather than the traditional barrel and barrel bushing. This makes the gun slightly more compact and easier to disassemble. The recoil system is quite unique for this style of 1911 as we use a solid, one piece guide rod and a flat recoil spring that is rated for 15,000 rounds in 9mm. That is 15,000 rounds! Not 500 rounds like most 1911 dual recoil systems are rated for. This is unheard of in a production 1911! This recoil system also gives the benefit of a smooth slide for easier operation and less felt recoil.
Trigger pull, like all of our 1911s, is short and crisp at around 4 lbs. This helps achieve the accuracy you’ve come to expect from a Dan Wesson.  The frame is anodized aluminum and features an undercut trigger guard and 25 LPI checkering. The mainspring housing is also aluminum with 25 LPI checkering and a rounded bottom corner for concealability and shooting comfort. These features coupled with the Ed Brown high ride grip safety and our new slim line DW carry G10 grips really help you hold onto the gun for faster follow-up shots and recoil control. Just like our Guardian, the ECO slide and small parts are treated with our Duty finish.
If you’re looking for a compact, lightweight and reliable 1911 that beats the competition, look no further than our ECO. We are confident you won’t be disappointed.
all firearm laws apply, must sign bill of sale, surrender pistol permit or have chp.  No shipping at this time, glad to meet at any local gun store to complete sale....
